Package: rugplot
Type: Package
Title: ReUsable Graphics
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Venustiano Soancatl-Aguilar
Maintainer: Venustiano Soancatl-Aguilar <v.soancatl.aguilar@rug.nl>
Description: The aim of the rugplot, R package based on ggplot, is to accelerate the creation of high quality visualization plots. Using 'rugplot', visualizations can be created in three simple steps. First, create a JSON parameters file. Second, read the rugplot parameters file and third, run a visualization function. It is possible to easily create different plots including labels, colors, dimensions, resolutions and save them in different file formats such as interactive and LaTeX pdf graphics.
